<h1>Mercury LaTeX Reference</h1><p>Type any expression below followed by <strong>Space</strong> to auto-render it. Click rendered math to edit parameters, hover to format.</p><h2>How It Works</h2><p>Anything you'd write inside <code>$$</code> or <code>\begin{align}</code> in LaTeX works here — just type it and press space. No delimiters needed.</p><h2>Greek Letters</h2><p><strong>Lowercase:</strong> \alpha \beta \gamma \delta \epsilon \varepsilon \zeta \eta \theta \vartheta \iota \kappa \lambda \mu \nu \xi \pi \varpi \rho \varrho \sigma \varsigma \tau \upsilon \phi \varphi \chi \psi \omega</p><p><strong>Uppercase:</strong> \Gamma \Delta \Theta \Lambda \Xi \Pi \Sigma \Upsilon \Phi \Psi \Omega</p><h2>Subscripts &amp; Superscripts</h2><p>These render without any backslash prefix:</p><p>x_{n+1} — subscript with braces</p><p>a^2 — simple superscript (single char)</p><p>x_{i}^{2} — both sub and superscript</p><p>A_{ij}^{kl} — multiple indices</p><h2>Fractions</h2><p>\frac{a}{b} — standard fraction</p><p>\dfrac{dy}{dx} — display-style fraction</p><p>\tfrac{1}{2} — text-style (small) fraction</p><h2>Summation &amp; Products</h2><p>\sum_{i=1}^{n} x_i — summation (click to edit bounds/body)</p><p>\prod_{i=1}^{n} x_i — product (click to edit bounds/body)</p><p>\coprod_{i} A_i — coproduct</p><h2>Integrals</h2><p>\int_{a}^{b} f(x)\,dx — definite integral</p><p>\iint_{D} f(x,y)\,dA — double integral</p><p>\iiint_{V} f\,dV — triple integral</p><p>\oint_{C} F\cdot dr — contour integral</p><h2>Limits</h2><p>\lim_{x \to \infty} f(x) — limit (click to edit variable/target/expression)</p><p>\limsup_{n \to \infty} a_n — limit superior</p><p>\liminf_{n \to \infty} a_n — limit inferior</p><h2>Big-O &amp; Asymptotic Notation</h2><p>\mathcal{O}(n) — Big-O</p><p>\mathcal{O}(n \log n) — Big-O log-linear</p><p>\Omega(n) — Big-Omega (use capital Omega)</p><p>\Theta(n^2) — Big-Theta (use capital Theta)</p><p>o(n) — little-o (just type: o(n) won't auto-render since it looks like text, use \operatorname{o}(n) or the math editor)</p><p>\omega(1) — little-omega</p><h2>Roots</h2><p>\sqrt{x} — square root</p><p>\sqrt[3]{x} — cube root</p><h2>Matrices</h2><p>Type then press space (click rendered matrix to add/remove rows/columns):</p><p>\begin{pmatrix} a &amp; b \\ c &amp; d \end{pmatrix} — parenthesized</p><p>\begin{bmatrix} 1 &amp; 0 \\ 0 &amp; 1 \end{bmatrix} — bracketed</p><p>\begin{vmatrix} a &amp; b \\ c &amp; d \end{vmatrix} — determinant</p><p>Also: matrix (plain), Bmatrix (curly), Vmatrix (double vertical)</p><h2>Cases / Piecewise</h2><p>\begin{cases} x &amp; x \geq 0 \\ -x &amp; x &lt; 0 \end{cases}</p><h2>Aligned Equations</h2><p>\begin{aligned} x &amp;= a + b \\ y &amp;= c + d \end{aligned}</p><h2>Binomial Coefficients</h2><p>\binom{n}{k} — binomial coefficient</p><p>\dbinom{n}{k} — display style</p><h2>Operators</h2><p>\sin \cos \tan \sec \csc \cot — trig functions</p><p>\arcsin \arccos \arctan — inverse trig</p><p>\sinh \cosh \tanh — hyperbolic</p><p>\log \ln \exp — logarithm/exponential</p><p>\max \min \sup \inf \arg \det \gcd \deg \dim \hom \ker</p><h2>Relations</h2><p>\leq \geq \neq \approx \equiv \sim \simeq \cong \propto</p><p>\subset \supset \subseteq \supseteq \subsetneq \supsetneq</p><p>\in \notin \ni</p><h2>Arrows</h2><p>\rightarrow \leftarrow \Rightarrow \Leftarrow \leftrightarrow \Leftrightarrow</p><p>\implies \iff \to \mapsto</p><p>\uparrow \downarrow \Uparrow \Downarrow</p><p>\nearrow \searrow \swarrow \nwarrow</p><p>\hookrightarrow \hookleftarrow</p><h2>Set Theory &amp; Logic</h2><p>\forall \exists \nexists \emptyset \varnothing</p><p>\cup \cap \bigcup \bigcap \setminus</p><p>\neg \lor \land \implies \iff</p><h2>Decorations &amp; Accents</h2><p>\hat{x} \bar{x} \vec{v} \dot{x} \ddot{x} \tilde{x}</p><p>\widehat{abc} \widetilde{abc}</p><p>\overline{AB} \underline{text}</p><p>\overbrace{x+y}^{n} \underbrace{a+b}_{k}</p><p>\overset{?}{=} \underset{x}{f}</p><h2>Miscellaneous Symbols</h2><p>\infty \partial \nabla \ell \hbar \aleph</p><p>\times \div \cdot \pm \mp \oplus \otimes</p><p>\cdots \ldots \vdots \ddots</p><p>\dagger \ddagger \star \circ</p><p>\Re \Im \wp</p><h2>Delimiters</h2><p>\left( \frac{a}{b} \right) — auto-sized parentheses</p><p>\left[ x \right] — auto-sized brackets</p><p>\left\{ x \right\} — auto-sized braces</p><p>\langle x \rangle — angle brackets</p><p>\lfloor x \rfloor — floor</p><p>\lceil x \rceil — ceiling</p><h2>Text &amp; Fonts in Math</h2><p>\text{if } x &gt; 0 — normal text within math</p><p>\mathbb{R} \mathbb{N} \mathbb{Z} \mathbb{Q} \mathbb{C} — blackboard bold</p><p>\mathcal{L} \mathcal{F} — calligraphic</p><p>\mathfrak{g} — Fraktur</p><p>\mathbf{v} — bold math</p><p>\mathrm{d}x — roman (upright)</p><h2>Spacing</h2><p>\quad — wide space</p><p>\qquad — double wide space</p><p>\, — thin space (use within integrals: \int f(x)\,dx)</p><h2>Display Math</h2><p>For centered, larger display-style math, wrap with \[ and \]:</p><p>\[ \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{x^k}{k!} = e^x \]</p><h2>Cancellation &amp; Boxing</h2><p>\cancel{x} \bcancel{x} \xcancel{x} — strikethrough</p><p>\boxed{E = mc^2} — boxed equation</p>